HEADWORD: Sematology
<hw>Sem`a*tol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>sh^ma</grk>, <grk>sh`matos</grk>, sign + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The doctrine of signs as the expression of thought or reasoning;
the science of indicating thought by signs.</def>
<rj><au>Smart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> semantics.</syn>
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

